narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Maybe. You watch good movies with a knowledgeable professor. The class is split roughly 60/40 between lecture and discussion, and the discussions were often much stronger than the lectures. Since I hadn't seen any older French movies before (either New Wave or earlier) this class was great because it exposed me to French cinema. I also felt that I got a good grasp on these movies through the lectures/discussion. Still, this class could get boring, especially during the detail-dense lectures.
Yeah I'd recommend the course to another student if they were already interested in film and wanted to learn more.
A summary of the history of French cinema, from the 1930's to the New Wave. A collection of films and texts are used for reference.
